SECURITIES. THESE NET REALIZED INVESTMENT GAINS WERE PARTIALLY OFFSET BY $14 MILLION OF NET REALIZED INVESTMENT LOSSES ASSOCIATED WITH U.S. TREASURY FUTURES CONTRACTS (WHICH REQUIRE DAILY

MARK-TO-MARKET SETTLEMENT AND ARE USED TO SHORTEN THE DURATION OF THE COMPANY'S FIXED MATURITY PORTFOLIO) AND $8 MILLION OF NET REALIZED INVESTMENT LOSSES RELATED TO OTHER

INVESTMENTS.

