("UNDERLYING LOSS AND LOSS ADJUSTMENT EXPENSE RATIO") WAS 3.7 POINTS LOWER THAN THE 2011 RATIO ON THE SAME BASIS, PRIMARILY REFLECTING THE FACTORS DISCUSSED ABOVE.

