REMAINED

STRONG BUT WERE LOWER THAN IN 2011. RENEWAL PREMIUM CHANGES REMAINED POSITIVE IN 2012 AND INCREASED OVER 2011, PRIMARILY DUE TO RENEWAL RATE INCREASES. NEW BUSINESS VOLUME IN 2012 DECLINED FROM 2011.

NET WRITTEN PREMIUMS IN 2012 WERE FAVORABLY IMPACTED BY POSITIVE AUDIT PREMIUM ADJUSTMENTS. NET WRITTEN PREMIUMS OF $2.78 BILLION IN 2011 INCREASED BY 2% OVER 2010. BUSINESS RETENTION RATES

REMAINED STRONG AND WERE CONSISTENT WITH 2010. RENEWAL PREMIUM CHANGES IN 2011 IMPROVED OVER 2010 DUE TO GROWTH IN BOTH RENEWAL RATE CHANGES AND INSURED EXPOSURES. NEW BUSINESS VOLUME IN 2011 DECLINED

FROM 2010.

